summary: This document is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) automated notification email indicating that a user at CBP-March AFB AMOC accessed a lookout query record for Jeffrey Epstein on January 4, 2023. It shows continued law enforcement interest in Epstein's records years after his death.

keyFacts: Jeffrey Epstein's law enforcement lookout record (P3N06596100A01) was accessed by CBP personnel on January 4, 2023, years after his death.
The access occurred at CBP-March Air Force Base (AFB) AMOC (Air and Marine Operations Center).
The document is an automated email notification from CBP's system triggered by the record access.
The query was performed by 'TASPD' (likely a CBP unit or system user).
This indicates ongoing law enforcement or intelligence interest in Epstein's records and travel history.
